WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.701
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYS]

00:12.751 --> 00:16.799
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:16.929 --> 00:20.846
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:20.977 --> 00:24.372
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.502 --> 00:28.332
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.463 --> 00:31.205
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

00:31.335 --> 00:33.990
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

00:36.775 --> 00:38.473
♪ 'CAUSE I'M
ALWAYS READY ♪

00:38.603 --> 00:42.694
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.480 --> 00:49.484
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

00:49.614 --> 00:51.486
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR

00:51.616 --> 00:53.357
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

00:53.488 --> 00:56.012
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:56.708 --> 00:59.798
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

00:59.929 --> 01:02.932
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.993 --> 01:22.908
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:23.039 --> 01:26.086
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:29.480 --> 01:33.397
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

01:33.528 --> 01:37.445
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR,
NO DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

01:37.575 --> 01:40.100
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.883 --> 01:43.886
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.016 --> 01:46.454
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:00.946 --> 02:02.905
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

02:05.299 --> 02:06.996
-MITCH: WELL, UTAH
WAS ALWAYS IN THE PICTURE.

02:07.127 --> 02:09.346
I MEAN, STOCKING
TO BELONG.

02:09.477 --> 02:11.043
-DONNA: YEAH.

02:11.174 --> 02:12.480
-MITCH: BUT I DON'T
KNOW, MY MONEY'S ON THE LAKERS.

02:12.610 --> 02:14.612
-DONNA: OH, ME
TOO! SHAQ'S THE MAN, HUH?

02:14.743 --> 02:15.657
-MITCH: HE'S THE MAN.

02:20.140 --> 02:22.707
-HEY, WHAT'S THAT BARGE
DOING SO CLOSE TO SHORE?

02:24.970 --> 02:26.972
-THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.
LET ME BORROW THE BINOCS.

02:30.193 --> 02:31.368
LOOKS LIKE HE'S ANCHORED
RIGHT IN FRONT OF

02:31.499 --> 02:32.500
THE SAND AND SEA CLUB.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.154
-THAT'S FUNNY.

02:34.284 --> 02:35.416
WELL, HAVE YOU
TALKED TO NEELY

02:35.546 --> 02:37.244
SINCE SHE STARTED
WORKING THERE?

02:37.374 --> 02:38.941
-NO, NO, I THOUGHT SHE WAS
STILL STAYIN' AT YOUR CONDO.

02:39.071 --> 02:40.377
-NO. SHE MOVED OUT.

02:40.508 --> 02:41.639
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE SHE'S LIVING.

02:44.599 --> 02:46.122
-WELL, I THINK IT'S TIME TO
HAVE A LITTLE TALK WITH HER.

02:46.253 --> 02:47.079
HERE YA GO.

02:47.906 --> 02:48.777
HAVE A GOOD DAY, HUH?

02:48.907 --> 02:49.778
-SEE YA.

02:52.302 --> 02:54.261
-[SOFT ROCK MUSIC]

03:15.107 --> 03:16.196
-HERE, GIRL,
KEEP THE CHANGE.

03:20.983 --> 03:21.853
-YO!

03:22.593 --> 03:23.638
-HEY!

03:23.768 --> 03:25.074
-[ROCK MUSIC]

03:27.859 --> 03:30.688
-HEY, YOU REALLY SHOULD
WATCH WHERE YOU'RE GOIN'.

03:39.567 --> 03:40.394
-JERK.

03:45.399 --> 03:46.443
-HEY, CAROLINE!

03:46.574 --> 03:47.401
-HI!

03:51.274 --> 03:52.841
UH, LIEUTENANT, HI.

03:52.971 --> 03:54.582
-CAROLINE! WHAT
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

03:54.712 --> 03:56.018
-WELL, I'M ON HIATUS.

03:56.148 --> 03:57.498
-BUT YOU'RE NOT ON
THE SOAP ANY MORE?

03:57.628 --> 03:58.803
-OH, I AM. MY CHARACTER
WENT OFF TO EUROPE.

03:58.934 --> 04:00.022
SO, I HAVE A
COUPLE WEEKS OFF.

04:00.588 --> 04:01.763
I WAS HOPING TO
GET IN A FEW DAYS

04:01.893 --> 04:03.243
SO I COULD KEEP
ON ACTIVE ROSTER.

04:03.373 --> 04:06.028
-YEAH. I'VE SEEN YOU
ON SHANNON'S HOPE.

04:07.508 --> 04:09.510
-SO, DO YOU THINK YOU CAN
FIT ME INTO THE SCHEDULE?

04:09.640 --> 04:10.467
-YA KNOW WHAT,
YOU'RE IN LUCK.

04:10.598 --> 04:11.990
NEWMIE CALLED IN SICK.

04:12.121 --> 04:13.340
I CAN ACTUALLY PUT
YOU IN A TOWER TODAY.

04:13.470 --> 04:14.645
-OH, THAT'S GREAT!

04:14.776 --> 04:16.168
OH, BUT PLEASE NOT
MOTHER'S BEACH.

04:16.298 --> 04:17.605
-I THINK YOU'RE READY
FOR THE REAL THING

04:17.735 --> 04:19.084
AS LONG AS YOU'RE
NOT TOO JET LAGGED.

04:19.214 --> 04:20.172
-NOT AT ALL. I SLEPT
THE ENTIRE FLIGHT.

04:20.303 --> 04:22.000
-GOOD!

04:22.130 --> 04:24.264
WELL, GO CHANGE AND I'LL LET
YA KNOW WHERE I NEED YOU.

04:24.394 --> 04:25.265
-THANK YOU.

04:33.708 --> 04:34.796
-[LAUGHTER]

04:34.926 --> 04:36.319
-ALL RIGHT. STEADY.

04:39.627 --> 04:40.802
-YOU OKAY?

04:40.932 --> 04:42.064
-THANK YOU. THANK
YOU. THANK YOU.

04:42.194 --> 04:43.631
-SURE. NO PROBLEM. SEE YA.

04:49.811 --> 04:50.812
-'SCUSE ME GUYS.

04:50.942 --> 04:51.726
-MAN: SEE YA.

04:51.856 --> 04:52.988
-HEY!

04:53.118 --> 04:54.250
-MITCH: HEY,
HOW YA DOIN'?

04:54.381 --> 04:56.252
-GOOD! HOW ARE YOU?
-[LAUGHS]

04:57.645 --> 04:58.820
WELL!

04:58.950 --> 05:00.212
QUITE A DISPLAY
YOU GOT GOIN' ON.

05:00.343 --> 05:02.563
-OH, THEM? JUST
TRYIN' TO BE FRIENDLY.

05:02.693 --> 05:04.956
-NO, NO. MEANING THE
FIREWORKS DISPLAY.

05:05.087 --> 05:05.870
THE BARGE OUT THERE.

05:06.001 --> 05:07.568
-OH. THAT.

05:08.133 --> 05:10.048
YEAH, ONE OF THE MEMBERS
IS GETTING MARRIED.

05:11.789 --> 05:13.051
-WELL, I HOPE YOU
GOT ALL THE PERMITS.

05:13.835 --> 05:15.489
-YEAH, THEY'RE ON
FILE IN THE OFFICE

05:16.098 --> 05:17.273
IF YOU'D LIKE
TO SEE EM.

05:17.404 --> 05:18.709
-NO, NO, NO, I
DON'T NEED TO SEE EM.

05:18.840 --> 05:20.407
I JUST WANT YOU
TO BE CAREFUL.

05:20.929 --> 05:23.845
ANY TIME YOU GOT A BARGE
MOORED THAT CLOSE TO THE BEACH,

05:23.975 --> 05:25.412
YOU'VE GOT LOTS OF
PROBLEMS WITH SWIMMERS,

05:25.542 --> 05:28.893
THE JOKERS, THE SURFERS,
YOU JUST DO ME A FAVOR,

05:29.024 --> 05:29.981
KEEP AN EYE ON IT.

05:30.112 --> 05:31.243
-YOU GOT IT!

05:32.636 --> 05:34.116
-LATE NIGHT?

05:34.246 --> 05:35.552
-OH, NO, THE BRIDE HAD
A BACHELORETTE PARTY.

05:36.074 --> 05:38.947
I'D NEVER BEEN TO ONE
BEFORE AND NOW, I KNOW WHY.

05:40.992 --> 05:43.168
-YOU KNOW, I'VE HARDLY SEEN
YOU SINCE YOU'VE BEEN BACK.

05:43.299 --> 05:45.475
I MEAN, WHAT'S
GOIN' ON?

05:45.606 --> 05:46.824
YOU LIKE IT HERE?

05:46.955 --> 05:48.696
-OH, ARE YOU
KIDDING? I LOVE IT!

05:48.826 --> 05:51.960
THEY'RE ACTUALLY TALKIN' ABOUT
MAKING ME SOCIAL DIRECTOR.

05:52.787 --> 05:53.657
-GREAT.

05:56.617 --> 05:58.923
-WELL, I BETTER
GET BACK.

05:59.924 --> 06:01.839
MAKE SURE TO SAY HI TO
EVERYONE FOR ME, WILL YA?

06:01.970 --> 06:02.927
-I WILL.
-OKAY.

06:04.755 --> 06:08.585
-NEELY, GLAD THINGS
ARE WORKIN' OUT FOR YA.

06:09.281 --> 06:10.326
-YEAH.

06:10.457 --> 06:12.067
HEY, DO YOU KNOW
IF MY DISABILITY

06:12.197 --> 06:13.155
CHECK HAS COME IN YET?

06:13.285 --> 06:14.461
-NO, BUT I'LL CHECK.

06:14.591 --> 06:15.287
I'M ON MY WAY BACK
TO HEADQUARTERS.

06:15.418 --> 06:16.288
-THANKS.

06:17.942 --> 06:18.856
HEY, MITCH!

06:21.685 --> 06:23.644
YOU SHOULD STOP BY
FOR A DRINK SOMETIME.

06:24.949 --> 06:25.820
-I WILL.

06:28.431 --> 06:30.433
-[SOFT MUSIC]

06:39.050 --> 06:40.356
-JD: I GUESS
THE RUMOR'S TRUE.

06:41.923 --> 06:42.967
-WHAT RUMOR IS THAT?

06:44.142 --> 06:46.275
-JD: THAT THE TOAST OF
NEW YORK IS BACK IN LA.

06:48.756 --> 06:49.757
-DID YOU MISS ME?

07:09.516 --> 07:10.386
-[DOOR CLOSES]

07:11.474 --> 07:13.433
-WELL, WELL. THAT
DIDN'T TAKE LONG.

07:14.434 --> 07:16.740
CAROLINE, YOU'RE
AT TOWER 25.

07:16.871 --> 07:18.481
-OH, WE'RE
DOUBLING UP.

07:18.612 --> 07:19.526
-NO.

07:21.092 --> 07:22.833
-I THOUGHT I
WAS AT 25.

07:22.964 --> 07:24.400
-THAT WAS BEFORE I CAUGHT
YOU IN THE LADIES LOCKER ROOM.

07:25.314 --> 07:27.185
NOW, YOU'RE WORKING
THE SWITCHBOARD.

07:36.107 --> 07:36.978
-YES!

07:40.677 --> 07:45.421
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

08:09.750 --> 08:12.013
-[FIREWORK EXPLOSION]

08:27.637 --> 08:28.595
-[JD ON PHONE]:
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

08:28.725 --> 08:29.987
-JD, THIS IS DONNA.

08:30.118 --> 08:31.511
CAN YOU ASK THE
LIEUTENANT IF THERE'S

08:31.641 --> 08:32.903
SUPPOSED TO BE FIREWORKS
ON THE BARGE RIGHT NOW?

08:33.034 --> 08:34.251
-JD: THEY'RE
JUST TESTING.

08:34.383 --> 08:35.775
-JUST TESTING.
ALL RIGHT, THANKS.

08:57.319 --> 09:00.365
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

09:14.597 --> 09:16.294
-JD: BAYWATCH,
GO AHEAD.

09:16.425 --> 09:18.035
-THIS IS DONNA. THERE'S BEEN
AN EXPLOSION ON THE BARGE.

09:18.166 --> 09:20.516
WE NEED FIRE BOATS ON
THE SCENE OFF AVENUE 24.

09:20.647 --> 09:21.909
-ANYONE HURT?

09:22.039 --> 09:23.824
-ONE MAN DOWN.
NEELY'S ON IT.

09:25.913 --> 09:29.569
-[SIRENS]

09:35.226 --> 09:37.794
-[COUGHING]

09:41.798 --> 09:43.583
-[GRUNTING]

09:58.206 --> 10:01.296
-[SIRENS]

10:17.791 --> 10:19.967
-[SCREAMS]

10:23.666 --> 10:25.189
-[SIRENS]

10:37.506 --> 10:38.725
-WOAH!

10:51.607 --> 10:53.827
[COUGHING AND GRUNTING]

10:56.830 --> 10:58.745
-NEELY, GET HIM
AWAY FROM THE BARGE!

11:12.062 --> 11:13.411
-[GASP]

11:19.635 --> 11:21.463
-[GRUNTING]

11:24.335 --> 11:26.207
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

11:29.123 --> 11:30.690
-[YELLING]

11:38.610 --> 11:40.700
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

11:45.269 --> 11:47.141
-[SIRENS]

12:07.161 --> 12:08.118
-YOU OKAY?

12:10.164 --> 12:11.339
-GET HER BACK
TO THE BEACH!

12:11.469 --> 12:12.601
-NEELY: HE'S
STILL UNDER!

12:14.646 --> 12:16.083
-[FIREWORKS EXPLODING]

12:18.912 --> 12:23.351
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

12:29.357 --> 12:30.706
-[INHALES SHARPLY]

13:01.693 --> 13:03.086
-CAROLINE, LETS...

13:04.479 --> 13:05.567
LET'S GET HIM
TO THE BEACH.

13:05.697 --> 13:06.611
-CAROLINE: OKAY.

13:09.658 --> 13:11.355
-HE WAS FIGHTING ME.
I COULDN'T HANG ON!

13:15.055 --> 13:15.882
-HE'S NOT BREATHING.

13:16.012 --> 13:17.927
-NO PULSE. BEGIN CPR.

13:18.058 --> 13:19.407
-CAROLINE: ONE, TWO.

13:19.537 --> 13:22.149
-MITCH: ONE, TWO,
THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

13:22.279 --> 13:23.454
-CAROLINE: BREATHE.

13:23.585 --> 13:24.586
-ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE.

13:24.716 --> 13:25.805
-CAROLINE: BREATHE.

13:26.806 --> 13:29.852
-MITCH: ONE, TWO,
THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

13:29.983 --> 13:31.071
-CAROLINE: BREATHE.

13:32.376 --> 13:37.120
-MITCH: ONE, TWO,
THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

13:37.251 --> 13:38.078
-CAROLINE: BREATHE.

13:40.471 --> 13:44.040
-MITCH: ONE,
TWO, THREE,

13:44.998 --> 13:47.478
FOUR, FIVE.
-[PULSING SOUND]

13:47.609 --> 13:48.566
-CAROLINE: BREATHE.

13:49.785 --> 13:51.743
-[INTENSE SLOW MUSIC]

13:53.397 --> 13:54.268
-[LOUD EXPLOSION]

13:56.400 --> 13:58.054
-WE GOT A PULSE.
-HE'S BREATHING.

13:58.185 --> 13:59.403
-ALL RIGHT, GET THE
BACKBOARD IN HERE!

13:59.534 --> 14:00.709
-LIFEGUARD: COMING.

14:00.840 --> 14:01.710
-LET'S GO!

14:03.364 --> 14:04.495
-CAROLINE: OKAY,
ON THREE.

14:05.105 --> 14:06.802
ONE, TWO, THREE.

14:15.724 --> 14:18.640
-OKAY, ONE, TWO, THREE.

14:18.770 --> 14:19.946
[GRUNTS]

14:22.557 --> 14:23.906
-HE'S IN.

14:24.037 --> 14:25.125
-ALL RIGHT, GET HIM
TO THE BURN UNIT.

14:25.255 --> 14:26.126
-GOT IT.

14:27.431 --> 14:28.258
ROLL ON.

14:28.389 --> 14:29.999
-[SIRENS]

14:39.052 --> 14:39.879
-NEELY.

14:42.229 --> 14:43.360
NEELY!
[NEELY GASPS]

14:45.232 --> 14:46.450
WHAT THE HELL
HAPPENED OUT THERE?

14:47.277 --> 14:49.976
-HIS SUIT WAS WATER LOCKED.
HE'S TOO HEAVY FOR ME.

14:50.759 --> 14:52.630
HEY, THANKS
FOR THE ASSIST.

14:52.761 --> 14:53.762
YOU CAME AT
A GOOD TIME.

14:53.893 --> 14:54.981
-NO, NO, NO, NO.

14:56.460 --> 14:57.505
WHERE WAS
YOUR RESCUE CAN?

14:58.723 --> 15:00.377
WHERE WAS
YOUR RESCUE CAN?

15:01.813 --> 15:03.337
YOU LISTEN TO ME.

15:03.467 --> 15:05.208
YOU MAY WANNA BE THE
SOCIAL ACTIVITIES DIRECTOR

15:05.339 --> 15:07.558
AROUND HERE, BUT UNTIL THEN,
YOU'RE STILL A LIFEGUARD.

15:09.082 --> 15:10.213
ACT LIKE ONE.

15:20.006 --> 15:21.442
-YEAH, I KNOW.
WELCOME BACK.

15:21.572 --> 15:22.530
-I'LL TALK TO
YOU LATER.

15:24.967 --> 15:27.187
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

15:30.146 --> 15:31.495
-[SIGHS]

15:51.863 --> 15:52.734
-WHAT'S WITH NEELY?

15:52.864 --> 15:54.083
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

15:54.214 --> 15:55.606
-YOU KNOW WHAT
I'M TALKIN' ABOUT.

15:55.737 --> 15:56.868
SHE WENT INTO THE WATER
WITHOUT HER RESCUE CAN.

15:56.999 --> 15:58.305
SHE COULDN'T
HANDLE HER VICTIM

15:58.435 --> 16:00.133
AND SHE DAMN NEAR
DROWNED OUT THERE.

16:00.263 --> 16:01.917
-WELL, MAYBE SHE JUST
LOST CONTROL FOR A MINUTE.

16:02.048 --> 16:03.353
IT CAN HAPPEN.

16:03.484 --> 16:05.268
-NO, SHE'S SLOPPY.
SHE'S NOT HERSELF.

16:05.399 --> 16:06.704
THERE'S SOMETHING
DIFFERENT ABOUT HER.

16:07.705 --> 16:09.490
DONNA, YOU
LIVED WITH HER.

16:09.620 --> 16:10.970
IS THERE SOMETHING
I SHOULD KNOW?

16:14.277 --> 16:15.409
-MITCH, I...

16:19.456 --> 16:20.501
SHE'S MY FRIEND.

16:22.764 --> 16:26.594
-IF SHE'S IN TROUBLE, A
FRIEND WOULD TRY AND HELP HER.

16:27.595 --> 16:28.988
-SHE'S HOOKED ON PILLS.

16:29.597 --> 16:30.424
-PILLS?

16:30.554 --> 16:32.295
-VICODIN, I THINK.

16:32.426 --> 16:34.558
SHE STARTED TAKING THEM WHEN
SHE INJURED HER BACK SKIING

16:34.689 --> 16:36.821
AND NOW, SHE CAN'T
STOP TAKING THEM.

16:36.952 --> 16:38.649
-THAT'S WHY SHE LEFT
BAYWATCH AND TOOK THE JOB

16:38.780 --> 16:40.216
AT THE BEACH CLUB.

16:40.347 --> 16:41.609
-YEAH, SHE KNEW THAT
SOMEONE WOULD FIND OUT

16:41.739 --> 16:43.219
IF SHE TOOK THE
PHYSICAL FOR RECHECK.

16:44.481 --> 16:46.918
I'M SORRY, MITCH. I SHOULD
HAVE SAID SOMETHING.

16:47.049 --> 16:48.746
-YEAH! YOU SHOULD
HAVE SAID SOMETHING.

16:48.877 --> 16:50.618
THAT GUY COULD HAVE
DIED OUT THERE!

16:50.748 --> 16:54.491
DONNA, NEELY COULD
HAVE DIED OUT THERE.

16:54.622 --> 16:55.710
-I UNDERSTAND NOW.

16:57.407 --> 16:58.495
WHAT ARE WE GOING TO DO?

17:02.673 --> 17:04.109
-[SIGHS]

17:04.240 --> 17:05.415
-CAROLINE: WELL, MY
SHIFT'S ALMOST OVER,

17:05.546 --> 17:06.982
SO I'LL MEET YOU
AT HEADQUARTERS?

17:07.113 --> 17:08.636
-I DON'T GET OFF FOR
ANOTHER HALF AN HOUR.

17:08.766 --> 17:11.595
-OKAY, WHY DON'T YOU MEET
ME IN THE LOCKER ROOM?

17:12.422 --> 17:13.249
-TWIST MY ARM.

17:14.990 --> 17:16.512
OH BOY. I GOTTA GO.

17:16.644 --> 17:17.645
I'LL SEE YOU, OKAY?

17:17.775 --> 17:18.646
-BYE.

17:19.603 --> 17:20.560
-[PHONE CLICKS]

17:21.605 --> 17:24.868
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

17:32.529 --> 17:33.878
-BUSY DAY, HUH?

17:34.749 --> 17:36.881
WOW, YOU MUST HAVE
ABOUT 10 GRAND THERE.

17:44.933 --> 17:46.195
ALL RIGHT, IN
THE BAG NOW!

17:46.326 --> 17:48.067
COME ON!
-CLERK: OKAY, OKAY.

17:49.155 --> 17:50.112
-THIEF: HURRY UP!

17:56.379 --> 17:58.686
COME ON! HURRY
UP! COME ON!

18:03.038 --> 18:04.779
IN THE BAG.

18:08.652 --> 18:13.004
-[INTENSE MUSIC]

18:16.095 --> 18:17.574
COME ON! HURRY UP!

18:17.705 --> 18:18.967
COME ON! LET'S GO!

18:19.098 --> 18:19.968
WHAT ARE
YOU LOOKIN' AT?

18:21.187 --> 18:22.449
ALL RIGHT.

18:23.667 --> 18:25.452
-HEY! HEY!

18:26.975 --> 18:28.237
-WOAH!

18:30.370 --> 18:32.546
-WHAT ARE YOU
DOING? CRAZY!

18:35.026 --> 18:38.987
-[TIRES SCREECHING]
-[SIRENS]

18:42.033 --> 18:46.516
[INTENSE MUSIC]

19:30.038 --> 19:31.126
-KEEP DRIVING!

19:31.257 --> 19:32.171
-WHAT? WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?

19:32.301 --> 19:33.346
-GET OUTTA THE WAY!

19:35.435 --> 19:36.262
-CAROLINE: GO?
GO WHERE?

19:36.392 --> 19:37.393
-I DON'T CARE.

19:37.524 --> 19:38.960
-LOOK, I CAN'T.
-JUST GO!

19:39.090 --> 19:40.266
I'M RUNNING OUT OF ROOM!

19:40.396 --> 19:41.876
-HIT THE BEACH.

19:42.006 --> 19:43.791
-WHAT? I CAN'T HIT THE
BEACH. NOT AT THIS SPEED.

19:43.921 --> 19:46.359
-I SAID HIT THE BEACH.

19:47.751 --> 19:49.797
-[TIRES SCREECHING]

19:54.497 --> 19:55.281
-GO!

19:55.411 --> 19:56.369
-WHAT THE HELL?

20:03.114 --> 20:04.681
-KEEP DRIVIN'!

20:07.380 --> 20:08.207
-DAMN!

20:10.774 --> 20:13.647
-[ROCK MUSIC]
-[SIRENS]

20:22.656 --> 20:25.441
THEY'RE GAININ' ON
US. DRIVE! DRIVE!

20:28.357 --> 20:29.967
-[GUN SHOTS]
-AH! AH!

20:30.098 --> 20:31.404
-THIEF: WOO HOO!

20:35.495 --> 20:36.365
-AH!

20:38.149 --> 20:39.673
-THIS IS BUCHANNON
HEADED SOUTH

20:39.803 --> 20:41.327
ON VENICE BEACH IN PURSUIT
OF A LIFEGUARD TRUCK.

20:41.457 --> 20:43.720
POSSIBLE KIDNAPPING.
CAROLINE'S ON BOARD.

20:43.851 --> 20:45.548
SHOTS ARE BEING FIRED.

20:45.679 --> 20:48.247
-WOO! COME ON!

20:49.335 --> 20:51.380
-[GUNSHOTS]

20:51.511 --> 20:52.555
-THIEF: HEY,
WATCH OUT!

20:56.167 --> 20:57.691
-[LOUD CRASH]

20:57.821 --> 20:59.214
-[CAROLINE GRUNTS]

21:11.139 --> 21:12.183
-STAY HERE!

